@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
                        @{b}@{fg shine}TruePub V1.3  (13.10.1996)@{ub}@{fg text}

               @{b}Public Screen Promoter for Non-Public Screens@{ub}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}


TruePub is a small program for promoting practically @{i}any @{ui}screen into @{"public" link "Index" 0}
one. Though small in size, TruePub offers full range of features. It can be
started from CLI (auto-detaching, no need to run it) or from Workbench. System
commodity properties are supported but not required. No reasonable limits
exist for preferences that can be given as CLI arguments or Workbench
tooltypes as well as in an external preferences file. All command, expression
and argument parsing is done with system-friendly routines.


                          @{"    Introduction    " link "Intro" 0}

                          @{" How does it work?  " link "Theory" 0}

                          @{"    Installation    " link "Install" 0}
