@node "Index" "TruePub - Index"
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}
                               @{b}The Index@{ub}
@{b}---------------------------------------------------------------------------@{ub}


@{u}Child process@{uu}

When started for the first time, TruePub leaves a so called child process in
the memory. This way the main program can exit soon after starting and there
is no need for "running" (when started from CLI or shell). The child is also
responsible for handling commodity messages. The @{"quit" link "Usage" 0} option removes child
process from the memory.

@{u}Public screen@{uu}

Unlike custom screens, public screens can be used by other programs too. For
example, making the screen of FinalWriter (famous word processor) public would
allow one to have EqEd (equation editor program) opened on the very same
screen. This easies doing things as you don't have to jump between Workbench
and FinalWriter screens all the time.
@endnode

